  "texts": [
    "MethodAs shown in Figure 5, TOPSIS is a distance-based technique that Hwang and Yoon [24] proposed in 1981.",
    "The TOPSIS technique makes it easy to define the positive and negative ideal solutions by presuming that each criterion tends to monotonically increase or reduce use.",
    "A Euclidean distance approach is suggested to assess how closely the alternatives resemble the ideal solution.",
    "The preferred order of the alternatives will be determined by a series of comparisons of their relative distances.",
    "The general principle behind this approach is that the optimal option should be closest to the ideal solution and the farthest distance from the negative ideal solution."
